- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is likely because the paper introduces an extension of call-by-push-value (CBPV) analysis to dependent type theory (DTT), which is a topic of interest in programming language research. 
- cs.TL (Type Theory) is likely because the paper specifically deals with dependent types and their interaction with computational effects, which is a topic within type theory. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is possible because the paper discusses the syntax and semantics of the dCBPV- and dCBPV+ systems, which can be seen as formal languages with associated automata. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is possible because the paper discusses operational semantics and subject reduction, which are important concepts in software engineering for ensuring the correctness and safety of programs.
